  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2007-01-16", 
    "text": "Amends the National Security Act of 1947 to require the head of an element of the intelligence community (IC), no later than 24 hours after receiving a request for information regarding an officer, employee, or agent of such element from a federal department, agency, or office that is not an element of the IC, to report such request to the Attorney General and the congressional intelligence committees. Revises the definition of \"covert agent\" for purposes of such Act."
  }, 
